The paper discusses the design of decision support systems for visualizing and mitigating cyber risks in the supply chain, specifically from IoT technologies. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as software engineering (cs.SE) since the paper proposes a methodology for designing decision support systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for risk assessment, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also touches upon the use of shared infrastructure in legacy supply chain systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
